<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[777,1372,2107,2528]" lastBlockId="5.[160,1368,2535,3474]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
The species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huet" authorityYear="1885" box="[992,1123,2260,2293]" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Chrysochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucorhina">leucorhina</taxonomicName>
was previously placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pomel" authorityYear="1848" box="[931,1088,2308,2333]" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Amblysomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblysomus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1799" box="[1115,1280,2308,2333]" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Chrysochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Chrysochloris</taxonomicName>
, Chlo- rotalpa, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mivart" authorityYear="1867" box="[972,1120,2343,2372]" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Calcochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Calcochloris</taxonomicName>
(subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forcat" authorityYear="1942" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Huetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Huetia</taxonomicName>
), based on various cranial and dental characteristics. Subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forcat" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[1160,1249,2418,2451]" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Huetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Huetia</taxonomicName>
was afforded full generic status by R. J. Asher and colleagues in 2010, based on phylogeny derived from combined morphological and molecular characteristics. Subspecies leucorhinanow includes other described taxa such as congicus and luluanus. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="synonymic_list">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6624513" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6624513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6624513/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" targetBox="[161,753,2115,2529]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1368,2535,3474]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[164,564,2657,2686]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Subspecies and Distribution.</emphasis>
